                           <history>
                              <origin>
                              <origDate notBefore="1897">
                              The land grant was issued by King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> on <date calendar="ethiopian" when-custom="1889-06-27" when="1897-03-05">27 Yakkātit 1889 year of mercy (= 5 March 1897 CE)</date>. 
                              The document provides a list of lands in various parts of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6569Tegray">Tǝgrāy</placeName> (32 places) which King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> donated as <foreign xml:lang="gez">gʷǝlt</foreign> and
                                 <foreign xml:lang="gez">rǝst</foreign> to Rās <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6668Mangasa">Mangašā Yoḥannǝs</persName> and his two children after the battle of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1264Adwa">ʿAdwā</placeName>(<date when="1896">1896</date>). 
                                 On <locus target="#193r"/> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName>ʼ expedition against the Italians, their defeat at ʿAdwā is mentioned. Subsequently Rās <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6668Mangasa">Mangašā Yoḥannǝs</persName>ʼs visit to the court in Addis Ababa is recounted. 
                                 The manuscript was tightly appended to <ref target="#p1"/>, possibly sewn into <ref target="#q22"/>, sometime after the document was issued.
                              </origDate>
                              </origin>
                           </history>
